I think you are talking about the mosquito sound system many kids turned into thier cellphone ringtones.

http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/06/13/AR2006061301557_pf.html

When I was a kid they had hearing tests in school. Everyone would put on headphones and they would play different low/high pitched frequency tones and if you could hear a sound you would raise your hand. I found it interesting not everyone could hear all the tones being played. But it is the same with this, many hear it but most who dont tend to be in the over 20 age bracket. There were some studies done as to why but you will have to google for those.

Misty


